  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
function set_attribute_value(attribute: String, value: <link href="../GLib-2.0/GLib.Variant.html">GLib.Variant</link>): void {
    // Gjs wrapper for g_menu_item_set_attribute_value()
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Sets or unsets an attribute on <code>menu_item</code>.</p>  <p>The attribute to set or unset is specified by <code>attribute</code>. This
can be one of the standard attribute names %G_MENU_ATTRIBUTE_LABEL,
%G_MENU_ATTRIBUTE_ACTION, %G_MENU_ATTRIBUTE_TARGET, or a custom
attribute name.
Attribute names are restricted to lowercase characters, numbers
and '-'. Furthermore, the names must begin with a lowercase character,
must not end with a '-', and must not contain consecutive dashes.</p>  <p>must consist only of lowercase
ASCII characters, digits and '-'.</p>  <p>If <code>value</code> is non-<code>null</code> then it is used as the new value for the
attribute.  If <code>value</code> is <code>null</code> then the attribute is unset. If
the <code>value</code> <link href="../GLib-2.0/GLib.Variant.html">GLib.Variant</link> is floating, it is consumed.</p>  <p>See also <link xref="Gio.MenuItem.set_attribute"/> for a more convenient way to do
the same.</p>
  <p>Since 2.32</p>
